Metric: Monthly Recurring Revenue
Description: Normalized monthly subscription revenue from all active paying customers. Annual contracts are pro-rated to their monthly equivalent. Excludes one-time fees, usage-based overages, and accounts in trial.
Owner: revenue-ops
Tags: mrr, saas, revenue, subscription, board-metric

Source: subscriptions, invoices

Given the subscription status is "active" or "past_due"
  And the plan is not "trial" or "free"
  And the billing interval is "monthly" or "annual"

When we calculate
  Then take the plan amount for each qualifying subscription
  And normalize annual plans by dividing the yearly charge by 12
  And sum across all qualifying subscriptions

The result is "Monthly Recurring Revenue"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 4 hours
  Null rate on plan_amount must be less than 0%
  Null rate on billing_interval must be less than 0%
  Null rate on status must be less than 0%
  Row count of subscriptions must not drop more than 5% day over day
  Value must be between 1000 and 50000000
  Value must not change more than 15% month over month
